text:
What to do on a stormy day?

Go to the beach and photograph the lighthouse.

Wind was gusting around 45-52 mph (according to forecast), hard to stand straight, sandstorm on the beach, sand stinging my face, trying to protect the camera & lens, difficult to hold the camera steady, challenging changing lenses, took 100s of shots trying to get the best waves.

© All my images are copyright. Please respect copyright.

Thank you.

Πρωτοφανείς καταστροφές έχει αφήσει στο πέρασμά της από την Καρδίτσα η κακοκαιρία «Ιανός», καθώς 5.000 σπίτια μέσα στην πόλη έχουν πλημμυρίσει, ενώ σοβαρές καταστροφές έχουν υποστεί και 15 χωριά. Σύμφωνα με τον μέχρι στιγμής απολογισμό, δύο άνθρωποι έχουν χάσει τη ζωή τους, σε Καρδίτσα και Φάρσαλα.

Πρόκειται για μία ηλικιωμένη γυναίκα, η οποία εντοπίστηκε νεκρή στο χωριό Βασιλί, στα Φάρσαλα κι έναν 63χρονο κτηνοτρόφο που αγνοείτο από την Παρασκευή στη Μαγουλίτσα Καρδίτσας.

Waves crashing everywhere, wind gusting around nearly knocking you over and blowing spray in your face and the camera. I was trying to capture the drama, the power of the waves, and the feel of being there. But after I got caught out by a huge wave and got soaked I retired to the safety of the sea wall, got myself a coffee from the cafe, and just sat watching instead.

text:
Μεγάλες ζημιές και καταστροφές προκάλεσε ο μεσογειακός κυκλώνας "Ιανός" στα επτάνησα και στην παράκτια Δυτική Ελλάδα. Μεγάλες ποσότητες βροχής και ισχυροί άνεμοι (επίπεδα θύελλας) καταγράφηκαν απο τους Α.Μ.Σ του Εθνικού Αστεροσκοπείου Αθηνών  αλλά και άλλων δικτύων. Απο το μεσημέρι και μετά, τα έντονα φαινόμενα επηρέασαν και περιοχές της ηπειρωτικής χώρας, με την περιοχή της Θεσσαλίας και της Φθιώτιδας να βρίσκονται στο επίκεντρο. Τις επόμενες ώρες θα συνεχιστούν οι έντονες βροχές σε μεγάλο μέρος της Κεντρικής Ελλάδος.

LIVE οι καιρικές συνθήκες σε όλη την χώρα :

http://stravon.gr/pinakas

The Medicabe "Ianos" caused great damage and destruction in the Ionian Islands and in coastal Western Greece. Large amounts of rain and strong winds (storm levels) were recorded by the AMS of the National Observatory of Athens and other networks. From noon onwards, the intense phenomena affected areas of the mainland. More specifically areas of Thessaly and Fthiotida are observed a large amount of rain. In the next few hours, heavy rains will continue in much regions of Central Greece.

text:
Medicane 'Ianos' pounds central Greece, leaves two dead ATHENS (GREECE) - A rare storm, known as Medicane (Mediterranean hurricane), lashed central Greece on Saturday, causing flooding, said authorities.

Named "Ianos", the storm uprooted trees and snapped power lines on the Ionian islands and the western Peloponnese on Friday. It then made its way to central Greece, hitting areas near Karditsa and Farsala.

Fire brigade officials retrieved the body of a woman from a flooded house in a hamlet near Farsala.

Police said search is going on for two more people who went missing when the storm hit.

Firefighters also stumbled upon the body of a man near a hospital in Karditsa.

Pounded by rains, the city of Karditsa resembled a lake as shown in television footage. One bridge collapsed in the storm.

"We're dealing with a total catastrophe," Nikolaos Gousios, a resident at Farsala, said.

Train services between Athens and Thessaloniki have been suspended.

The fire brigade said they got more than 2,450 calls for help when the storm hit to rescue people trapped in houses, remove uprooted trees and bail out water from shops and homes.

Efforts are underway to restore power supply in Karditsa and the Ionian islands. On Friday, five vessels sank off Zakynthos and Lefkada, said the coast guard.
